ants":[{"name":"Milford","meanings":["English (mainly Devon): habitational name from any of the many places called Milford, deriving from Old English <i>myln</i> ‘mill’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’.","Irish (Antrim and Galway): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maolfhoghmhair</b> ‘descendant of <i>Maolgfhoghmhair</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘chief of harvest’. The Irish name was first Anglicized as <b>Mullover</b>, which was later assimilated to <i>Milford</i>. See also   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Palmiere","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Dante, Enrico, Nicola, Salvatore, Vittorio.","Italian: from <i>palmiere</i> ‘palmer, pilgrim’. See   Palmer  ."]},{"name":"Parmer","meanings":["English: variant of   Palmer  .","Indian (northern states): variant of   Parmar  ."]},{"name":"Palmore","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Palmer   or an Americanized form of South German   Balmer  ."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":2,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Ann Palmer of Angmering was born in 1380, in Angmering, Sussex, England, her father, Adam Palmer, was 26 and her mother, Mrs Adam Palmer, was 27. She married Lord Robert Julian in 1399, in Angmering, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1440, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1380–1440":"1380–1440","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1354–1384":"1354–1384","1354–Female":"1354–Surnud","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1399":"1399","1354":"1354","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Angmering, Sussex, England":"Angmering, Sussex, England","Scotland":"Scotland","Preston, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Preston, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1380–1440":"1380–1440","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1354–1384":"1354–1384","1354–Female":"1354–Kuollut","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1399":"1399","1354":"1354","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Angmering, Sussex, England":"Angmering, Sussex, England","Scotland":"Scotland","Preston, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Preston, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1380–1440":"1380–1440","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1354–1384":"1354–1384","1354–Female":"1354–Décédée","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1399":"1399","1354":"1354","1375":"1375","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Angmering, Sussex, England":"Angmering, Sussex, Angleterre","Scotland":"Écosse","Preston, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Preston, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Lady Ann Palmer of Angmering est née en 1380, à Angmering, Sussex, Angleterre, son père, Adam Palmer, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Mrs Adam Palmer, avait 27 ans. Elle a épousé Lord Robert Julian en 1399, à Angmering, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 2 filles. Elle est décédée en 1440, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 60 ans."},"de":{"1380–1440":"1380–1440","1375–1435":"1375–1435","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1354–1384":"1354–1384","1354–Female":"1354–